Package org.jboss.windup.rules.apps.javaee.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DataSourceModel
    Represents a data source within the application.
    EjbBeanBaseModel
    Contains metadata used by all specializations of EJBs (eg, environment references)
    EjbDeploymentDescriptorModel
    Contains metadata associated with EJB deployment descriptors.
    EjbEntityBeanModel
    Contains EJB Entity information and related data.
    EjbMessageDrivenModel
    Contains EJB Message Driven model information and related data.
    EjbSessionBeanModel
    Contains EJB Session Bean information and related data.
    EnvironmentReferenceModel
    Represents an <env-ref> entry from a Java deployment descriptor (eg, web.xml).
    HibernateConfigurationFileModel  
    HibernateEntityModel
    Contains metadata associated with a Hibernate Entity
    HibernateMappingFileModel
    Contains metadata extracted from a hibernate mapping file (*.hbm.xml)
    HibernateSessionFactoryModel
    Contains metadata related to Hibernate Session Factories.
    Jbpm3ProcessModel  
    JmsConnectionFactoryModel
    Represents a JMS Connection Factory that is defined or referenced by the application.
    JmsDestinationModel
    Represents a JMS Message destination.
    JNDIResourceModel
    Represents a JDNI resource found within the application.
    JPAConfigurationFileModel
    Contains a graph model representing a JPA configuration file within the application.
    JPAEntityModel
    Contains metadata associated with a JPA Entity
    JPANamedQueryModel
    Contains metadata associated with a JPA Named Query.
    JPAPersistenceUnitModel
    Contains metadata related to JPA Persistence Units.
    SpringBeanModel
    Contains metadata associated with a Spring Bean.
    SpringConfigurationFileModel
    Contains metadata extracted from the XML configuration file.
    WebXmlModel
    Represents the data from a Java EE web.xml file.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    JmsDestinationType
    Defines whether or not a JMS destination represents a JMS Topic or a Queue.
